attributes.name: Right lung
phrases:
2.1 x 2 cm
 diameter poorly defined nodule in periphery of the right upper lobe is
 associated with a pleural tag extending to the lateral pleural surface.

Multifocal bronchial wall thickening is present, particularly in the right
 perihilar region, but also within the infrahilar area on the lateral view.

2.  2 cm peripheral right upper lobe lung nodule is concerning for a lung
 cancer, likely adenocarcinoma subtype.

Considering clinical suspicion for infection and other
 multifocal abnormalities in the chest on the current study, it may be
 reasonable to first complete a course of antibiotic therapy prior to CT.
